itemListElement.name: Food Tour and Scavenger Hunt in Pike Place Market

name: Food Tour and Scavenger Hunt in Pike Place Market
description:
This 2 hour walking food and fun tour though Pike Place Market is perfect for all ages!

On this tour you will explore the cultural significance of the country’s oldest continuously running farmers market, all the while sampling some of the best food the city has to offer! 

But that’s not all! A friendly, local and experienced guide will lead you through a Market scavenger hunt that will stimulate all 5 of your senses. From the smell of fresh flowers, to the booming voices of fish mongers, to the vibrant colors of local produce, you’ll experience the Market in a way you can’t get anywhere else! There will be prizes, surprises, and if you’re not careful, you just might learn something.

Our busy, local market can be intimidating for newcomers. Let us make its uniqueness more accessible for you.

Your ticket includes a tasting menu of some of our favorite foods from 6 local businesses. There is enough food that you’ll want to show up with room in the belly, but not starving.

address.streetAddress: 519 E Pine St, Seattle, WA 98122 NEKO: A Cat Cafe

itemListElement.name: Breathe In Seattle City Walking Tours

name: Breathe In Seattle City Walking Tours
description: On tour you will get to learn about Seattle from a historic, geographic and cultural perspective which appeals to all ages. Our tours are designed to give guests as much of the Seattle experience as possible within a reasonable time-frame and each place covered on tour is discussed in-depth. The number of sights shown and areas of the city covered would normally take much longer to navigate and much of the historical relevance of the places we visit would be lost. This tour offers a fresh look at Seattle which leaves guests with a new appreciation for the city's art, history and culture.

name: Pike Place Market Dessert Tour
description: Whether you are visiting Seattle's Pike Place for the first time or are a born and raised local, Thoughtful Chef Tours offers a unique glimpse into the culture and history of this iconic open air market. This two hour guided walking tour leads our guests through a behind-the -scenes journey to seven local vendors, where they are able to enjoy a variety of sweet treats while meeting artisan vendors and learning the history and secrets of the market. Space on each tour is limited to ensure each guest has a personalized experience, so reserve your spot today to guarantee you don't miss this tour of an integral piece of Seattle's roots.

name: Seattle Salmon Guided Fishing Trip
description: What is more uniquely Seattle than being able to fish for Salmon, Bottomfish, and Squid just minutes from downtown? Come join us as your US Coast Guard licensed Captain Paul Kim takes you out for a private trip on the scenic waters of Puget Sound. Guests will be treated to a memorable and exciting experience and have the opportunity at catching one of the hard fighting salmon that swims in our backyard. The puget sound is nestled between 2 majestic mountain ranges and on clear days, views of Mt. Rainier can be seen from our tours. If we're fortunate, we might see wildlife such as seals, harbor porpoise, various birds, and at times of the years Orca whales. All trips originate from the scenic Shilshole marina in the historic Ballard neighborhood.

review.name: Best fishing guide I’ve ever worked with!
review.reviewBody: My son & I had an amazing time fishing with Captain Paul. He’s boat is state of the art, clean, and fish finding equipment spot on. I will definitely go out with him again fishing on our next trip out.  We caught & released our Salmon limit very quickly & continued fishing throughout the morning. Best time ever!!!

review.name: Catching fish and bonding with my teenage daughter
review.reviewBody: Went out with Captain Paul for a daddy-daughter excursion. The boat was very well maintained and had all the equipment we needed. All we did is show up dressed in our waterproof gear. While we wanted to go for salmon unfortunately they are not in season. However flounder are, and we had a great day hooking them one after the other. She and I both had a blast. On our drive home she even said she would like to go out again sometime. We will carry happy memories of the day with us for the time to come. Captain Paul thanks for making this such a  memorable day.

review.name: Father & Son fishing trip
review.reviewBody: Awesome fishing trip with my son. Captain Paul Kim worked hard and got us into resident coho salmon. My son and I both caught two keepers. It was his first salmon and he wants to go back again. You wont find a nicer or more knowledgeable Captain.

name: Fresh Seafood Tacos
description:
This class is perfect for adults, kids and kids at heart to come together and enjoy what good cooking is all about!

An experienced chef will meet you at our kitchen at the Fisherman's Terminal - Seattle's largest, working terminal that houses commercial fishing vessels and a vibrant fish market and restaurant scene. 

All ingredients are locally and ethically sourced.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Sights: From Skyline Peaks to Aged Alleys

name: Seattle Sights: From Skyline Peaks to Aged Alleys
description: Embark on a journey where you and your loved ones traverse Seattle's best-kept secrets and iconic landmarks. Stand atop the Sky View Observatory, feeling the city's pulse from dizzying heights. Dive into architectural artistry at the Seattle Central Library, before immersing yourselves in the vibrant tapestry of Pike Place Market. As the Seattle Great Wheel slowly turns, let the cityscape unfold before your eyes, offering new vistas with each rotation. Our 'Best of Seattle Walking Tour' promises a captivating blend of history, culture, and scenic beauty, ensuring memories that your family will treasure forever.

itemListElement.name: Seattle’s Romantic Rendezvous: A Journey of Love

name: Seattle’s Romantic Rendezvous: A Journey of Love
description: Embark on a romantic journey through Seattle’s captivating landscapes and cultural landmarks. Your adventure begins at Kerry Park, where the breathtaking views of the city and Mount Rainier set a picturesque scene for a couple’s photo. Next, delve into the artistic heart of the city at Seattle Opera, celebrating the beauty of performance arts. Wander the lively grounds of Seattle Center, immersing yourselves in its rich cultural and entertainment offerings. Gaze up at the iconic Space Needle, an emblem of the city’s skyline, and finish your exploration at the Pacific Science Center, where interactive exhibits bring an element of playful discovery to your romantic excursion

itemListElement.name: Private Seattle Cooking Class with a Chef in Her Home

name: Private Seattle Cooking Class with a Chef in Her Home
description:
Born and raised in Seattle and a University of Washington graduate, Brittney is a true Seattleite. She cares deeply about eating local food that is sustainably produced and is excited to share with you what makes Pacific Northwest cuisine unique. Brittney graduated from culinary school and is now a personal chef focused on cooking whole-food, plant-based cuisine that helps prevent diabetes and heart disease. Visit her in her beautifully designed home with a view of Lake Union to learn to cook and enjoy healthy food that tastes great!

• Private cooking class in Seattle with a chef
• Immersive Pacific Northwest culinary and cultural experience
• Gourmet Pacific Northwest meal using local, seasonal and sustainable ingredients
• Vegetarian and vegan options are available, on request

review.name: Wonderful culinary experience with Brittney
review.reviewBody:
My wife, me and our two kids visited Brittney's home and cooked with her on my wife's birthday. It was a wonderful experience! All of us got to take part in the cooking process, we learned a lot from Brittney, prepared dishes we otherwise would've never got to taste, and the resulting meal was delicious. 
According to my wife, ​"I don't think if we'd gone to any restaurant in Seattle, it would've been as good as this!"

review.name: Delicious and fun
review.reviewBody: I got this class as a gift for my birthday and it was such a fun and delicious experience. Chef Brittney is such a great teacher and just a very wonderful person to talk to. She gave us some useful cooking and nutrition tips too that I know I’ll always use in my kitchen. And the food of course was absolutely delicious! I know I’ll make this dish again in the future. Thank you for making this birthday so special.

review.name: So fun and delicious!
review.reviewBody: I had such a great time cooking with Brittney in her beautiful home! She was so fun to chat with and she gave me so many valuable cooking tips. Her dogs were adorable and her home had a great view! Our lunch was delicious!

review.name: EXCELLENT CHEF EXPERIENCE
review.reviewBody: Brittney was amazing host to me and my friend. She taught us Knife techniques that I didn’t learn in Culinary. I brought my old classmate that I haven’t seen since 1997. This Chef experience set a positive precedent because it helped set the stage for stronger friendship relationship.I would definitely recommend the Chef experience to anyone that is trying propose to someone,first date,or person that is not into social interaction.

review.name: Wonderful culinary experience
review.reviewBody: Brittney is an expert chef and I was extremely happy to have been able to learn from her. Would recommend for all experience levels. Brittney also chose great ingredients and taught us how to select them ourselves. We were taught to cook halibut with an amazing chimmichurri sauce and more.

itemListElement.name: Mount Rainier Full Day Private Tour and Hike (Seattle)

name: Mount Rainier Full Day Private Tour and Hike (Seattle)
description:
Our guides team is made up of Master Naturalists, experts with Master's Degrees in Outdoor and Sustainability Education, and more! 

Marvel at the 14,410’ Tahoma (Mount Rainier) - the most prominent peak in the contiguous United States. You’ll join your local Good Trip Adventures guide for a day exploring the diverse volcanic landscape - from the dense old-growth forests at its base to the wildflower-dotted alpine meadows above. 

From the Sunrise area of the park, you’ll get an up-close view of the effects of the mountain’s power as your guide explains its geological history. The day is yours to customize and your guide will work with your group to design an itinerary perfectly suited to your abilities and interests.

name: Adult Pirate Party Cruise
description:
Adult Pirate Party Cruises are 21 and up (photo ID required at boarding). Party pirates are invited to Get Their Pirate On aboard Queen Anne’s Revenge. A raucous time will be had by all as we party our way around the Lake Washington Ship Canal and Lake Union.

Our pirates will have you up on your feet. Defend the honor of Queen Anne’s Revenge as we fire the ship’s water cannons (weather permitting). Enjoy games and contests on the cruise. Nightly prizes for the Best-Dressed Pirate.

Guests should arrive at Lake Union Park (860 Terry Ave N) at least 30 minutes prior to boarding time. Upon boarding, all party pirates receive a pirate name tag and all pre-ordered swag. Head to the ship’s store to purchase pirate swag not pre-ordered as well as snacks and beverages, including beer, wine and seltzer.

Outside food and beverages are not allowed. Boarding lasts 15-20 minutes. The cruise lasts approximately 1:15 minutes, with up to 15 minutes of disembark time, for a total of up to 1:45.

itemListElement.name: Luxury SUV Airport Transfer From SeaTac-Seattle (Up 6 Passengers)

name: Luxury SUV Airport Transfer From SeaTac-Seattle (Up 6 Passengers)
description:
At Suv Seattle Services, we offer a unique experience that stands out from ride-share companies. Our vehicles can carry up to six passengers, providing comfort and style for your trips. 

 • Lincoln Navigator
 • Chevy Suburban
 • Volvo XC90

All reservations are confirmed automatically, and we assign vehicles based on the number of passengers and availability.

Gratuity is not included.

review.name: Professional airport transfer service
review.reviewBody: Our driver was waiting for us for our 3:30 am pick-up, took care of our luggage, and quickly took us to the airport.  The driver was professional and helpful.  Perfect for two half-awake travelers!

review.name: Without a doubt … use these folks!
review.reviewBody:
I booked an airport transfer from Sea-TAC to our hotel in downtown Seattle because I figured things would be hectic arriving at prime time on a summer Friday afternoon. If you’ve never used a car service for transfers from large airports, they are worth it.

Seattle SUV is price competitive. Moreover, they went above the measure of above and beyond to get us where we needed to be when things didn’t go as planned at the airport.

Our plane landed on time but was held in the hinterlands for 15-20 minutes due to flight congestion. Our driver contacted us as planned and  I acknowledged. Once inside, the airport was overrun with people and our airline’s baggage service experienced a major meltdown. As Murphy’s law would allow, ours were among the last bags down the conveyor — an hour after the plane parked at the gate!

We were in regular communication with our driver throughout. It was very stressful, but we hung in there and so did Seattle SUV services. Once we got our bags, our driver picked us up promptly and got us to our hotel safely, VERY comfortably and with pleasant demeanor. A tip here — the gratuity is figured into your trip, but don’t hesitate to reward exceptional service with plenty extra!

A measure of a firm’s commitment to customers is not always how they do when things go right, but how they do when things go wrong. I can’t give these folks enough gold stars!

review.name: This service is worth the money!!
review.reviewBody: Rudy did a great job getting us from SeaTac to our hotel.  He communicated his arrival very well along with what he needed us to do so he could find us and get us loaded.  Seamless experience.  Worth the money and highly recommended

review.name: Our Seattle Hero
review.reviewBody:
First things first... Nikita, you're a hero! Texas weather has nothing on you and for that we couldn't have asked for a better experience.

Hope to book with company again soon.
